The paper proposes a new algorithm for solving Distributed Constraint Optimization Problems (DCOPs) by combining search and inference strategies. This topic falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of context-based inference, which is related to Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). Finally, the algorithm aims to optimize efficiency, which is relevant to Systems and Control (cs.SY).
